article.headline: Indiana St. 30, Youngstown St. 24
article.story: YOUNGSTOWN, Ohio -- Ronnie Fouch passed for 290 yards and four touchdowns to lead Indiana State to a 30-24 win over Youngstown State on Saturday. Fouch, who completed 16 of 23 passes and had one interception, had a 68-yard touchdown pass to Alex Jones and a 50-yard passing score to Bryant Kent to give the Sycamores (6-4, 4-3 Missouri Valley Conference) a 15-7 lead in the first quarter. Jarmaine Cook scored on a 5-yard run and Stephen Blose made a 19-yard field goal to give the Penguins (3-8, 1-7) a two-point advantage. But that was the last lead for Youngstown State, which lost its seventh straight in its season finale. Fouch threw an 11-yard touchdown pass to Kent and hooked up with Jones for an 8-yard passing score, giving Indiana State a 30-17 lead. Jones caught five passes for 147 yards for the Sycamores, while Kent had four catches for 79 yards.
